            "weighting": "<dd>50%</dd>",
            "due_date": "<dd><p> 17/09/2026 11:40 am</p>\n<p>\n</p><p>WEEK 8 (Thursday in class)</p></dd>",
            "learning_objectives": "L01, L02, L03, L04, L05, L06, L07, L08, L09, L10",
            "mode": "Written",
            "category": "Essay/ Critique, Examination",
            "task_description": "<div class=\"collapsible collapsible--text\">\n<p>In-class exam on L6, L7, L8 and other materials covered in class. The exam is comprised of two tasks: character writing and essay writing. The character writing focuses on words learned from each lesson. The essay writing focuses on using the rhetorical styles and other writing skills we have discussed in class.</p>\n<p>This assessment task is designed to enhance students’ ability to communicate with cultural sensitivity and engage thoughtfully in discussions on key issues relevant to both Australian and Chinese workplace contexts. Intercultural (Australia vs. China) and intracultural (indigenous perspectives) examples will be discussed and provided in class to help students prepare for the assessment. </p>\n<p>Check Blackboard for the marking rubric. </p>\n<p><strong>AI and MT Statement</strong></p>\n<p>This assessment task is to be completed in-person. The use of generative Artificial Intelligence (AI) or Machine Translation (MT) tools will not be permitted. Any attempted use of AI or MT may constitute student misconduct under the Student Code of Conduct.</p>\n<button class=\"collapsible__toggle\">\n<span class=\"collapsible__open link--icon icon--standard--arrow-down-1\">Read full task description</span>\n<span class=\"collapsible__close link--icon icon--standard--arrow-up-1\">Hide full task description</span>\n</button>\n</div>",
            "submission_guidelines": "<p>In person exam. Hand in paper when the exam ends.</p>",
            "deferral_or_extension": "<p>You may be able to <a href=\"https://my.uq.edu.au/information-and-services/manage-my-program/exams-and-assessment/deferring-exam#3\">defer this exam</a>.</p>",
            "late_submission": null,
            "additional_info": "<p>You may be able to <a href=\"https://my.uq.edu.au/information-and-services/manage-my-program/exams-and-assessment/deferring-exam#3\">defer this exam</a>.</p>"
        },
        {
            "assessment_detail_section_id": "assessment-detail-1",
            "assessment_title": "Reading and Oral Response Interview",
            "special_indicators": [
                {
                    "special_indicators_class": "icon--education--bookmarks-document icon-text--small",
                    "special_indicator_text": "Identity Verified"
                },
                {
                    "special_indicators_class": "icon--how-youll-learn--multiple-circle-1 icon-text--small",
                    "special_indicator_text": "In-person"
                }
            ],
            "weighting": "<dd>50%</dd>",
            "due_date": "<dd><p> 10/11/2026 3:00 pm</p>\n<p>\n</p><p>Students will be assigned a timeslot between 3-5 pm on Tuesday, Exam WEEK 1</p></dd>",
            "learning_objectives": "L01, L02, L03, L04, L05, L06, L07, L08, L09, L10",
            "mode": "Oral",
            "category": "Practical/ Demonstration, Presentation",
            "task_description": "<div class=\"collapsible collapsible--text\">\n<p>Time &amp; Date: 3:00 pm – 5:00 pm, Tuesday, November 10, 2026</p>\n<p>Venue: 32-415</p>\n<p>Assessment Note: Please be aware that the entire interview will be audio/video recorded for assessment and marking purposes.</p>\n<p>The entire interview consists of two main parts and will take approximately 12 minutes to complete. At the start, you will be handed two paragraphs selected directly from the main texts of the lessons covered after the mid-semester exam. You will have exactly 5 minutes of quiet time to read through these paragraphs and organize your thoughts. Please note that cell phones and dictionaries are not permitted for translation; however, you may use a pen or pencil to take notes or mark the text directly.</p>\n<p>Following your preparation time, you will begin the 7-minute interactive session by providing a concise summary of the paragraphs. The interviewer will then ask a series of questions based on the text. These will include direct questions to verify your understanding of specific details, as well as conceptual, open-ended, and follow-up questions that allow you to expand on the themes, express your opinions, or connect the reading to broader topics discussed in class. You may refer to your notes or the paragraphs throughout the interview without penalty.</p>\n<p>Check Blackboard for the marking rubric. </p>\n<p><strong>AI and MT Statement</strong></p>\n<p>This assessment task is to be completed in-person. The use of generative Artificial Intelligence (AI) or Machine Translation (MT) tools will not be permitted. Any attempted use of AI or MT may constitute student misconduct under the Student Code of Conduct.</p>\n<button class=\"collapsible__toggle\">\n<span class=\"collapsible__open link--icon icon--standard--arrow-down-1\">Read full task description</span>\n<span class=\"collapsible__close link--icon icon--standard--arrow-up-1\">Hide full task description</span>\n</button>\n</div>",
            "submission_guidelines": "<p>You may be able to <a href=\"https://my.uq.edu.au/information-and-services/manage-my-program/exams-and-assessment/applying-assessment-extension\">apply for an extension</a>.</p>",
